    explanation: "The argument establishes: can't hire a choreographer, so must cut dances. Cutting dances means failing to sell enough tickets to break even. The conclusion is that the production will not break even. The gap is between 'failing to sell enough tickets to break even' and 'not breaking even' — the production could theoretically break even through other revenue (donors, merchandise, etc.) despite poor ticket sales. Choice A closes this gap by ensuring that insufficient ticket sales guarantees not breaking even. Choice C is close but says other revenue is 'negligible,' which is less precise than A's direct logical bridge.",
