    type: "Flaw",
    stimulus: `An archaeologist argues that the ancient settlement at Kerno must have been a major trading hub. Her evidence is that artifacts made from materials not locally available — such as obsidian and copper — were found at the site. She reasons that since these materials could only have arrived through trade, the settlement must have been a center of commercial activity.`,
