    correct: "A",
    explanation: "Rivera explicitly argues that government mandates are necessary to ensure adequate cybersecurity. Chen directly counters that government-mandated standards would be counterproductive and that companies handle threats better on their own. They clearly disagree about whether government regulation would effectively improve cybersecurity. Choice C is tempting, but while Rivera implies current measures are inadequate, Chen's argument is not that current measures are adequate — it is that regulation would be worse than company-led responses. Choice D is not in dispute; both speakers appear to value data protection.",
