    id: 72,
    type: "Must Be True",
    stimulus: `All organic compounds used as food preservatives must be approved by the National Food Safety Board before they can be used commercially. Sodium benzoate is an organic compound currently used as a preservative in many commercial beverages. Recently, the board revoked approval for any preservative that has been shown to form benzene when combined with ascorbic acid under certain conditions. Sodium benzoate has been shown to form benzene when combined with ascorbic acid under certain conditions.`,
