    correct: "A",
    explanation: "The planners' argument depends on the assumption that commuters will actually switch from driving to the subway. Choice A provides strong evidence for this by citing studies showing that in comparable situations, a large majority of commuters do shift to subway use. This directly supports the claim that the extension will reduce congestion. Choice D is tempting because it shows stated preferences, but surveys of hypothetical behavior are weaker evidence than actual studies of behavior in comparable real-world situations. Choice B describes the severity of congestion but does not show that the subway would alleviate it.",
