    type: "Weaken",
    stimulus: `A food safety researcher argues that the recent increase in foodborne illness outbreaks in the country is caused by the growing popularity of organic farming, which does not use synthetic pesticides. She reasons that without synthetic pesticides, organic produce is more likely to harbor harmful bacteria, and as organic produce has gained a larger share of the market, more consumers have been exposed to contaminated food.`,
