    stimulus: `Recent observations have confirmed that all known exoplanets orbiting red dwarf stars within the habitable zone are tidally locked, meaning one side permanently faces the star. Any tidally locked planet experiences extreme temperature differences between its star-facing and dark sides. Atmospheric modeling shows that a planet with extreme temperature differences between its two sides can retain liquid surface water only if it has an atmosphere dense enough to circulate heat globally.`,
