    stimulus: `Critics of the scientific peer review system argue that it is biased because reviewers tend to favor research that aligns with established theories. However, an analysis of recently published papers reveals that roughly 30 percent of articles in top journals present findings that challenge prevailing scientific consensus. If the peer review system were systematically biased against unorthodox research, such a high proportion of paradigm-challenging publications would be unlikely.`,
